  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in most countries. It is a criminal activity that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money to make it appear legitimate. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement (introducing illegal funds into the financial system)\n2. Layering (concealing the source of the money through complex transactions)\n3. Integration (making the money appear legal and usable)\n\nMany countries have strict anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations to prevent and prosecute this type of financial crime. Penalties can include significant fines and imprisonment.",
